data.reasoningText:
All the types have static `Deserialize*` methods that take a `JsonElement`. This is much cleaner than using `ModelReaderWriter.Read`. So for deserialization, I can:

```csharp
// Before:
systemData = JsonSerializer.Deserialize<SystemData>(property.Value.GetRawText());
// After:
systemData = SystemData.DeserializeSystemData(property.Value);
```

This is much cleaner! The `property.Value` is already a `JsonElement`. No need to convert to string and back.

For `OperationStatusResult` self-reference:


Refactoring deserialization calls...

For `ManagedServiceIdentity`, I can use the same pattern with the static deserialize method. But `ResponseError` comes from Azure.Core, so it might not have a custom deserialize method available.

